docs.abstract: The European Union’s highest court decided the taste of a cheese does not qualify for protection.
docs.snippet: The European Union’s highest court decided the taste of a cheese does not qualify for protection.
docs.lead_paragraph: A Dutch cheese company tried to claim that it had a monopoly on the taste of a cheese spread. The Court of Justice of the European Union weighed arguments from two competing food producers, and decided on Tuesday that a taste cannot be copyrighted.

headline.main: Who Has the Copyright Over My Cheese?
headline.print_headline: E.U., Settling a Cheese Duel, Says Taste Can’t Be Copyrighted

docs.lead_paragraph: Carlos Ghosn, the man who created what was effectively the world’s largest carmaker, has been released on bail after spending more than three months in jail.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn Is Out of Jail. What Happens Next?

docs.abstract: Kristine E. Guillaume, of Queens, made it through a rigorous process to take charge of a student publication once run by Franklin D. Roosevelt.
docs.snippet: Kristine E. Guillaume, of Queens, made it through a rigorous process to take charge of a student publication once run by Franklin D. Roosevelt.
docs.lead_paragraph: Writers and editors at The Harvard Crimson have gone on to be presidents (John F. Kennedy, Franklin D. Roosevelt), tech billionaires (Steve Ballmer, the former chief executive of Microsoft), news media bosses (Jeff Zucker, the head of CNN) and a number of my colleagues at The New York Times. But what the newspaper had in power, it lacked in diversity.

headline.main: For the First Time, a Black Woman Will Lead The Harvard Crimson
headline.print_headline: New Leader Of Crimson Vows to Take It Into Future

docs.abstract: Breaking a silence, Caroline and Maya Ghosn said they suspected that talk of “reimagining the alliance” with Renault had played a role in their father’s ouster on allegations of financial misconduct.

docs.lead_paragraph: The children of Carlos Ghosn, the jailed auto executive who oversaw an alliance that sold more than 10 million cars a year, believe accusations of financial misconduct against him are part of a revolt within Nissan against exploring a possible merger with Renault.

headline.main: Carlos Ghosn’s Daughters See a Nissan Revolt Behind His Arrest

docs.abstract: A natural gas discovery could bolster the economy and revive the country’s regional clout. But Egyptians battling unemployment and inflation might gain little.
docs.snippet: A natural gas discovery could bolster the economy and revive the country’s regional clout. But Egyptians battling unemployment and inflation might gain little.
docs.lead_paragraph: CAIRO — President Abdel Fattah el-Sisi likes to flaunt his plans for modernizing Egypt, like the flashy new administrative capital rising from the desert outside Cairo. But most Egyptians view his rule as a time of painful belt-tightening, with soaring inflation, a currency crash and cuts to subsidies that have made fuel, electricity and water more expensive.

headline.main: Egypt Looks to Offshore Gas Field for Growth and Influence
headline.print_headline: Egypt Sees New Muscle In Discovery Of Gas Field

docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — Uber expects to be worth as much as $91 billion when it starts selling shares next month, making its initial public offering one of the largest in the history of the technology industry.

docs.lead_paragraph: Uber gave the first sign of how big its highly anticipated initial public offering might be, telling some investors that its stock sale might value it at up to $100 billion, people briefed on the matter said.
